I dont want root, mezz, charm or any other ability other classes use. I want to play a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> MAGE</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unaladini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>naladini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 434<br> <font color=#333333>(9/22/02 6:02:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hold Elemental proposed instead of Elemental Silence</span><hr size=1> If VI wants to expand our defensive ability against summoned creatures, I'm fine with that. While I've never been a mezzer, I've never been a rooter either, so it makes little difference to me which one we pick up. Its not something I think we really need, but it remains to be seen how the spell will fit into the game.<br>
<br>
If there's a zone where mages can solo against summoned creatures, I think root would be great.<br>
<br>
However, since VI will probably set this up so that we'll need to be in groups to be effective, here are the arguments against root:<br>
<br>
1) Root would cause your group to have to reposition the main mob away from the add in order to avoid getting beat on. <br>
<br>
2) A rooted mob could still summon someone (most likely the mage).<br>
<br>
3) When mez breaks, its effects go away completely (aside from a lot of hate for the caster). With Root, aggro management would be difficult unless your group waits for the effect to wear off before attacking.<br>
<br>
What I think will be interesting is if these summoned creatures can be mezzed by normal enchanter spells and bard songs, or if groups will NEED the mage version of the spell to actually mez (or root). Thereby making mages absolutely required for certain zones (finally for something other than rods).<br>
<br>
I wouldn't be surprised to see a lot more 'situational' spells for various classes.<br>
 <p>Naladini <BR>
