<br>
There are a few people arguing that they don't want root <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> instead of mez</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and there are people that appear to be saying they &quot;don't want&quot; root, when they probably mean they don't think mages should have root(or mez).  <br>
<br>
I sort of fall into both categories.  I think that if mages want mez they should group with an Enchanter.  The blurring of class lines since Luclin seems to be getting dangerously excessive at times...<br>
<br>
But...<br>
<br>
If I had to choose between root and mez I'd take mez.  I think it is out of character for the class but I like the idea of mezzing and even made a twink enchanter for that reason.  I also consider mez to be more powerful than root, the only drawback being that you cannot attack a mezzed mob without it breaking.  Consider a solo situation..  you send your pet in to attack a mob and cast root on the mob.  This accomplishes basically nothing unless your pet dies.  On the other hand, mez would halt the battle, giving you time to flee or med or heal your pet or decide on a new strategy... <br>
<br>
However, I so also think that root is equally out of character for the class.  Root doesn't really have anything more to do with summoning than mezzing, and niether of them fit what the class has historically done.<br>
<br>
However, looking at it from a roleplaying perspective, I think mez and charm are both very appropriate.  I have encountered it in books before(can't remember which at the moment, I'm thinking Eddings but I can't be sure)..  a summoner attempts to take control of his opponent's elemental.  It can be thought that the same powers the magician uses to call and dominate an elemental from another plane can, instead, be focused on elementals summoned by someone else.  Initial summons are inherently more stable, thus &quot;Charm/Mez Summoned&quot; are high level, unreliable or imperfect skills.<br>
<br>
Mez seems as if it is a charm that isn't quite strong enough to take full control.  The spell &quot;cast on you&quot; messages do seem more like a root, I will admit.  But this spdat message makes it seem like the mage summons something to hold the target..  which seems kind of silly to me because when you get right down to it you can accomplish anything via summoning.  You could say &quot;Soadnso flees in terror at the sight of the summoned apparition&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ushanre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shanre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(9/23/02 9:02:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hehehe</span><hr size=1> So if your soloing and mez a element - you gonna have a seriously pissed of mob comming at you.<br>
