My point here was to illustrate that there are still many players in the game that don't fully understand root. The proximity aggro with the root spell can give some of the other melees a false sense of security when fighting the mob (casters too). When root breaks, you could be in for a very sudden shift in aggro.<br>
<br>
1)That being said, I'd wager those players actually do have brains, they simply haven't been in a lot of situations where a mob has been rooted.<br>
<br>
2)To help avoid that situation, mez is a little nicer as it dispells as soon as your MA lands an attack. Only the caster is aware of when root breaks, so its one more thing the mage will need to watch for/announce.<br>
 <br>
To put it simply, root simply isn't as 'graceful' as mez.<br>
<br>
To respond to a few other comments, I do agree with the idea of being masters of summoned creatures, similar to necros and undead. If VI could simply add enough summoned mobs so they are 25% of the total undead population in the game, we'll probably do very well.<br>
